  "prompt": "What is the Nirvana song \"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" about?",
  "response": "According to Kurt Cobain, the song \"Smells Like Teen Spirit\" was not meant to have a deeply specific meaning. It was more about capturing a mood of teenage disillusionment and rebellion. The title itself came from a deodorant brand that his friend Kathleen Hanna spray-painted on a wall, which Cobain found amusing. \n\nThe song seems to express feelings of alienation, apathy, and frustration common among youth in the early 1990s. Its lyrics and frenetic musical style reflect a sense of disconnection and anger at societal expectations. Musically, it became an anthem for Generation X and helped bring alternative rock into mainstream popularity.\n\nWhile the exact meaning is somewhat ambiguous, the song is generally interpreted as a critique of conformity and a expression of youthful disenchantment with social norms and institutions.",
